attributes.title: Intro
attributes.body:
The purpose of the Building Understanding of Mothers during Pregnancy (BUMP) by 4YouAndMe is to better understand how your body changes during pregnancy.
The study will last from the time you agree to partecipate until about 6 weeks after giving birth.

attributes.title: Clinic visits
attributes.body:
We will ask you to stay about up to 30 minutes after each of your routine medical visits to take additional measurements and answer additional questions, including:
- Blood pressure
- measurements
- Pitting test
- Cognitive assessments
We will read information from your medical chart like your medical history, weight, and blood pressure and store it in the study database.

attributes.title: Study app
attributes.body:
Throughout the study, we will communicate with you using this app. We will send you notifications with announcements and reminders. You will use the app to perform the following activities:
- Daily surveys
- Daily cognitive assessments
- Video diaries
- Gait activity
- Step test

attributes.title: Devices
attributes.body: Throughout the study, you will wear a Fitbit and an Oura smart ring. You should wear these devices at all times and we suggest you to charge them when you shower. We will also give you a smart scale to keep in your home and use once every day.

attributes.title: Check-ins
attributes.body: A member of the study team may contact you in between your clinic visits to make sure you are doing the study tasks and wearing your devices. We will also answer any questions you have about the study.

attributes.title: Payments
attributes.body:
We will pay you up to $300 for your time and effort in participating in the study. You will gain points for wearing your devices, doing a daily weight-in, answering surveys, and performing active tasks. Once you reach 40 points we'll send you $10 via PayPal.
You will also get to keep your Fitbit and your Oura smart ring at the end of the study.

attributes.title: Possible benefits
attributes.body: While we hope to make advances in the understanding of pregnancy, it's important to know that you are not expected to get any benefit from taking part in this study.

attributes.title: Risks & discomforts
attributes.body:
We have put in place all possible measures to protect your information but there is always the small risk that people not connected with this study may learn your identity or personal information.
This study is no way providing medical advice. The data collected and presented to you through the app will not be reviewed by the study team in real time and is not considered medical information. If you have any questions about health or your pregnancy, please contact your doctor.

attributes.title: Voluntary
attributes.body: This study is completely voluntary and you can quit at any time without penalty. This will not impact your ability to receive medical care at Mount Sinai. If you decide to stop participating, please contact a member of the research team. At this point, no new data will be collected but the data already collected will be used and studied.

attributes.title: Confidentiality
attributes.body: As part of this study, the research team will use and share some of your private, protected health information with members of the research team, the research sponsor, collaborators and other researchers. You are protected by the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA).

attributes.title: Data sharing
attributes.body: By signing this consent, you are giving permission for your medical information to be stored and used for future research, related or unrelated to your medical condition, by investigators at Mount Sinai and outside of Mount Sinai. Some collaborators of the study sponsor, 4YouAndMe, are also interested in learning more about pregnancy. After your data is de-identified, it will be shared with these partners as detailed in this consent document.

attributes.title: Think about it
attributes.body: If you have any questions about the study, please contact the research team at 212-123-4567 or help@4youandme.org

attributes.title: Great Job!
attributes.body:
You've demonstrated good understanding of this study.
\n\nYou're almost there! Please take a minute to review the full consent form. Then if you're sure you'd like to join the study, you can sign the form.

attributes.title: Informed Consent
attributes.body: On the next screens, we will explain the research study and the impact it may have on your life. Then you'll have the option to consent to partecipate.

attributes.title: Uh, oh!
attributes.body:
It seems there are some things you need to review before joining this study. Please review the consent screens again and try again.
\nIt's important that you have a good understanding of the study before you start.

attributes.title: Consent comprehension questions
attributes.body:
Now that you have had a chance to read through the consent, we will ask you a few basic questions to see how well we did explaining the study to you. You will need to answer at least 4 of the following 5 questions correctly to be able to sign the consent form and partecipate in the study. Please take your time to read each question and select an answer.
If you don't answer the questions correctly on the first try, you will get a chance to try again.
